{{APIHeader|Plugins/Validation/Methods|accept|function}}
{{APIEntry|
|type=function
|name=accept
|cat=Plugins/Validation/Methods
|return=Boolean
|desc=Makes a file upload accept only specified mime-types.
|longdesc=|longdesc=Uses the HTML5 file API to look at the type attribute of one or more selected files and validate that each matches the specified mime-type.

If nothing is specified, only images are allowed (image/*).

You can specify multiple mime-types by separating them with a comma, e.g. "image/x-eps,application/pdf".

Works with type="file" inputs.

Note: This method used to look at just the filename, specifically the file extension. That behaviour is now available as the "extension" method inside additional-methods.js, same as this "accept" method itself.
|arg0=mimetype
|arg0type=String
|arg0desc=The allowed type, seperated via <nowiki>",", defaults to "image/*"</nowiki>
|arg0optional=true
}}

<noinclude>
